body:
Some expressions that contain `this` are broken with `--coverage` enabled since 34ced254c0b1ebcf996dd922266faabd26da1869 (@toddstrader).

For example, this:

```systemverilog
class Foo;
    function logic test;
        return !this;
    endfunction
endclass
```

Results in the following error:

```
Error: test.sv:3:17: Internal: Unknown node type reached emitter: THISREF
    3 |         return !this;
      |                 ^~~~
```

And this:

```systemverilog
class Foo;
    function logic test;
        return this && this;
    endfunction
endclass
```

Results in:

```
%Error: test.sv:3:16: Internal: Unknown node type reached emitter: THISREF
    3 |         return this && this;
      |                ^~~~
%Error: test.sv:3:24: Internal: Unknown node type reached emitter: THISREF
    3 |         return this && this;
      |                        ^~~~
```

It doesn't manifest for all expressions, e.g. a sole `this`, `this.x`, `f(this)` all work. Even `this + 1` is accepted (it breaks on C++ compilation :smile:). Seems like logic expressions are the problem.

Test case for completeness:

```systemverilog
class Foo;
    function logic test;
        return this && !this;
    endfunction
endclass

module t;
    initial begin
        Foo f = new;
        void'(f.test);
        $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```

